Merkel’s FDP Ally Wants Smart Power Grids Faster, Bild Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 
2011-03-19T13:44:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-19/merkel-s-fdp-ally-wants-smart-power-grids-faster-bild-reports.html
German Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s
Free Democrat allies want the country to speed up efforts to
build so-called “smart” power grids that are needed to
transport and store renewable energy, the  Bild Zeitung  said.  Free Democrat lawmakers want to enact a law that gives the
government special rights to override regional and local powers
over decision-making linked to the grids, the newspaper cited
FDP lawmaker  Marco Buschmann  as saying.  Such a move, prompted by the nuclear disaster in Japan,
could shrink the time needed to have a complete national
building plan for the grids to 2 years from a decade or longer,
Buschmann told the newspaper in an interview  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
